			h1 Getting Started
			p BitTorious supports several BitTorrent client. More may work, but it's imperative that your choosen client respects the "private" nature of torrents, as well as supports encryption of P2P file transfers. For this reason we recommend uTorrent, with Vuze as a fall-back option. We'll use uTorrent for the examples in this tutorial. A free version of uTorrent is available at <a href=http://www.utorrent.com>utorrent.com</a>. Please note that the sample screenshots were made using the uTorrent client for Mac and consequently may look a little different for Windows and Linux users.


